This paper deals with the optimization of unmanned aerial vehicle base stations (UAVBSs) for wireless communication networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves the allocation of resources and the use of algorithms, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also considers the capacity constraints of the network, which is related to control systems (cs.SY) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
